3459 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
3460 void TRailGraphics::ChangeTransparentColour(Graphics::TBitmap *BitmapIn, Graphics::TBitmap *BitmapOut, TColor NewTransparentColour, TColor OldTransparentColour)
3461 {
3462  // Change OldTransparentColour to NewTransparentColour, if NewTransparentColour not white change black to white
3463  // else change white to black
3464  if(NewTransparentColour == OldTransparentColour)
3465  {
3466  return; // already stored
3467 
3468  }
3469  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + ",ChangeTransparentColour," + AnsiString(NewTransparentColour) + "," +
3470  AnsiString(OldTransparentColour));
3471  BitmapOut->Height = BitmapIn->Height;
3472  BitmapOut->Width = BitmapIn->Width;
3473  for(int x = 0; x < BitmapIn->Width; x++)
3474  {
3475  for(int y = 0; y < BitmapIn->Height; y++)
3476  {
3477  if(NewTransparentColour != clB5G5R5) // new is dark, old could be dark or light
3478  {
3479  if(BitmapIn->Canvas->Pixels[x][y] == OldTransparentColour)
3480  {
3481  BitmapOut->Canvas->Pixels[x][y] = NewTransparentColour;
3482  }
3483  else if(BitmapIn->Canvas->Pixels[x][y] == clB0G0R0)
3484  // black - if OldTransparentColour was black (or any dark colour) then track will be white already
3485  {
3486  BitmapOut->Canvas->Pixels[x][y] = clB5G5R5; // white
3487  }
3488  else
3489  {
3490  BitmapOut->Canvas->Pixels[x][y] = BitmapIn->Canvas->Pixels[x][y];
3491  }
3492  }
3493  else
3494  {
3495  // new is white, old must be dark else new = old & wouldn't reach here
3496  if(BitmapIn->Canvas->Pixels[x][y] == OldTransparentColour)
3497  {
3498  BitmapOut->Canvas->Pixels[x][y] = NewTransparentColour;
3499  }
3500  else if(BitmapIn->Canvas->Pixels[x][y] == clB5G5R5) // white
3501  {
3502  BitmapOut->Canvas->Pixels[x][y] = clB0G0R0; // black
3503  }
3504  else
3505  {
3506  BitmapOut->Canvas->Pixels[x][y] = BitmapIn->Canvas->Pixels[x][y];
3507  }
3508  }
3509  }
3510  }
3511  BitmapOut->TransparentColor = NewTransparentColour;
3512  Utilities->CallLogPop(1795);
3513 }
3514 
3515 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
3516 
3517 void TRailGraphics::ChangeForegroundColour(int Caller, Graphics::TBitmap *BitmapIn, Graphics::TBitmap *BitmapOut, TColor NewForegroundColour,
3518  TColor BackgroundColour)
3519 {
3520  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",ChangeForegroundColour," + AnsiString(NewForegroundColour) + "," +
3521  AnsiString(BackgroundColour));
3522  BitmapOut->Height = BitmapIn->Height;
3523  BitmapOut->Width = BitmapIn->Width;
3524  for(int x = 0; x < BitmapIn->Width; x++)
3525  {
3526  for(int y = 0; y < BitmapIn->Height; y++)
3527  {
3528  if(BitmapIn->Canvas->Pixels[x][y] != BackgroundColour)
3529  {
3530  BitmapOut->Canvas->Pixels[x][y] = NewForegroundColour;
3531  }
3532  else
3533  {
3534  BitmapOut->Canvas->Pixels[x][y] = BackgroundColour;
3535  }
3536  }
3537  }
3538  Utilities->CallLogPop(1480);
3539 }

3541 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
3542 
3543 void TRailGraphics::ChangeForegroundColour2(int Caller, Graphics::TBitmap *BitmapIn, Graphics::TBitmap *BitmapOut, TColor NewForegroundColour,
3544  TColor BackgroundColour)
3545 {
3546  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",ChangeForegroundColour2," + AnsiString(NewForegroundColour) + "," +
3547  AnsiString(BackgroundColour));
3548  Graphics::TBitmap *TempBitmapOut = new Graphics::TBitmap;
3549 
3550  TempBitmapOut->Assign(BitmapIn); // in case BitmapOut isn't fully defined at this stage
3551  TRect FullRect(0, 0, BitmapIn->Width, BitmapIn->Height); // the full size of both bitmaps
3552 
3553  TempBitmapOut->Canvas->Brush->Color = BackgroundColour; // BrushStyle default is solid so leave at that
3554  TempBitmapOut->Canvas->FillRect(FullRect);
3555  for(int x = 0; x < BitmapIn->Width; x++)
3556  {
3557  for(int y = 0; y < BitmapIn->Height; y++)
3558  {
3559  if(BitmapIn->Canvas->Pixels[x][y] != BackgroundColour)
3560  {
3561  TempBitmapOut->Canvas->Pixels[x][y] = NewForegroundColour;
3562  }
3563  }
3564  }
3565  BitmapOut->Assign(TempBitmapOut);
3566  delete TempBitmapOut;
3567  Utilities->CallLogPop(2101);
3568 }

3570 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
3571 
3572 void TRailGraphics::ChangeSpecificColour(int Caller, Graphics::TBitmap *BitmapIn, Graphics::TBitmap *BitmapOut, TColor ColourToBeChanged, TColor NewColour)
3573 {
3574  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",ChangeSpecificColour," + AnsiString(ColourToBeChanged) + "," +
3575  AnsiString(NewColour));
3576  BitmapOut->Height = BitmapIn->Height;
3577  BitmapOut->Width = BitmapIn->Width;
3578  for(int x = 0; x < BitmapIn->Width; x++)
3579  {
3580  for(int y = 0; y < BitmapIn->Height; y++)
3581  {
3582  if(BitmapIn->Canvas->Pixels[x][y] == ColourToBeChanged)
3583  {
3584  BitmapOut->Canvas->Pixels[x][y] = NewColour;
3585  }
3586  }
3587  }
3588  Utilities->CallLogPop(1481);
3589 }

3591 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
3592 
3593 void TRailGraphics::ChangeBackgroundColour(int Caller, Graphics::TBitmap *BitmapIn, Graphics::TBitmap* BitmapOut, TColor NewBackgroundColour,
3594  TColor OldBackgroundColour, bool &ColourError)
3595 {
3596  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",ChangeBackgroundColour," + AnsiString(NewBackgroundColour) + "," +
3597  AnsiString(OldBackgroundColour));
3598  ColourError = false;
3599  BitmapOut->Height = BitmapIn->Height;
3600  BitmapOut->Width = BitmapIn->Width;
3601  bool OneChanged = false;
3602 
3603  for(int x = 0; x < BitmapIn->Width; x++)
3604  {
3605  for(int y = 0; y < BitmapIn->Height; y++)
3606  {
3607  if(BitmapIn->Canvas->Pixels[x][y] == OldBackgroundColour)
3608  {
3609  BitmapOut->Canvas->Pixels[x][y] = NewBackgroundColour;
3610  if(!OneChanged)
3611  {
3612  if(BitmapOut->Canvas->Pixels[x][y] != NewBackgroundColour)
3613  {
3614  // can be different if the palette of the pixel is different from that expected
3615  ColourError = true;
3616 // throw Exception("BackgroundColour change incorrect - actual = " + AnsiString((int)BitmapOut->Canvas->Pixels[x][y]) + ", expected " + AnsiString((int)NewBackgroundColour));
3617  }
3618  }
3619  OneChanged = true;
3620  }
3621  else
3622  {
3623  BitmapOut->Canvas->Pixels[x][y] = BitmapIn->Canvas->Pixels[x][y];
3624  }
3625  }
3626  }
3627  Utilities->CallLogPop(1482);
3628 }

3631 
3632 void TRailGraphics::ChangeBackgroundColour2(int Caller, Graphics::TBitmap *BitmapIn, Graphics::TBitmap* BitmapOut, TColor NewBackgroundColour,
3633  TColor OldBackgroundColour)
3634 {
3635 // superseded by ChangeBackgroundColour3 using direct pixel manipulation
3636  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",ChangeBackgroundColour2," + AnsiString(NewBackgroundColour) + "," +
3637  AnsiString(OldBackgroundColour));
3638  Graphics::TBitmap *TempBitmapOut = new Graphics::TBitmap;
3639 
3640  TempBitmapOut->Assign(BitmapIn); // in case BitmapOut isn't fully defined at this stage
3641  TRect FullRect(0, 0, BitmapIn->Width, BitmapIn->Height); // the full size of both bitmaps
3642 
3643  TempBitmapOut->Canvas->Brush->Color = NewBackgroundColour; // BrushStyle default is solid so leave at that
3644  TempBitmapOut->Canvas->FillRect(FullRect); // now all coloured same as new background
3645 
3646 // TempBitmapOut->Canvas->CopyMode = cmSrcAnd; //these lines instead of the for.. next pixel loop didn't work, they gave distorted
3647 // TempBitmapOut->Canvas->CopyRect(FullRect, BitmapIn->Canvas, FullRect); //colours, but worked OK without the Assign for a reason I couldn't fathom
3648 
3649  for(int x = 0; x < BitmapIn->Width; x++)
3650  {
3651  for(int y = 0; y < BitmapIn->Height; y++)
3652  {
3653  {
3654  if(BitmapIn->Canvas->Pixels[x][y] != OldBackgroundColour)
3655  {
3656  TempBitmapOut->Canvas->Pixels[x][y] = BitmapIn->Canvas->Pixels[x][y];
3657  }
3658  }
3659  }
3660  }
3661 
3662  BitmapOut->Assign(TempBitmapOut);
3663  delete TempBitmapOut;
3664  Utilities->CallLogPop(2102);
3665 }

3667 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
3668 
3669 void TRailGraphics::ChangeBackgroundColour3(int Caller, Graphics::TBitmap *BitmapIn, Graphics::TBitmap* BitmapOut, TColor NewBackgroundColour,
3670  TColor OldBackgroundColour)
3671 {
3672  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",ChangeBackgroundColour3" + AnsiString(NewBackgroundColour) + "," +
3673  AnsiString(OldBackgroundColour));
3674  Byte *SLPtrIn; // pointer to the ScanLine values in BitmapIn
3675  Byte *SLPtrOut; // pointer to the ScanLine values in TempBitmapOut
3676  Graphics::TBitmap *TempBitmapOut = new Graphics::TBitmap;
3677 
3678  TempBitmapOut->Assign(BitmapIn); // in case BitmapOut isn't fully defined at this stage
3679  int NewBGColourNumber = ColNametoNumber(0, NewBackgroundColour);
3680  int OldBGColourNumber = ColNametoNumber(1, OldBackgroundColour);
3681 
3682  for(int x = 0; x < BitmapIn->Height; x++)
3683  {
3684  SLPtrIn = reinterpret_cast<Byte*>(BitmapIn->ScanLine[x]);
3685  SLPtrOut = reinterpret_cast<Byte*>(TempBitmapOut->ScanLine[x]);
3686  for(int y = 0; y < BitmapIn->Width; y++)
3687  {
3688  if(SLPtrIn[y] == OldBGColourNumber)
3689  {
3690  SLPtrOut[y] = NewBGColourNumber;
3691  }
3692  else
3693  {
3694  SLPtrOut[y] = SLPtrIn[y];
3695  }
3696  }
3697  }
3698  BitmapOut->Assign(TempBitmapOut);
3699  delete TempBitmapOut;
3700  Utilities->CallLogPop(2103);
3701 }

3704 
3705 int TRailGraphics::ColNametoNumber(int Caller, TColor Colour)
3706 {
3707  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",ColNametoNumber" + AnsiString(Colour));
3708  int Number;
3709 
3710  if(Colour == clB0G0R0) // black //used these in place of case statements because 64 bit compiler issued warnings
3711  { //that not using the enum names, and several fell inbetween the enum names
3712  Number = 0x0;
3713  }
3714  else if(Colour == clB5G5R5) // white
3715  {
3716  Number = 0xd7;
3717  }
3718  else if(Colour == clBufferAttentionNeeded)
3719  {
3720  Number = 0x23;
3721  }
3722  else if(Colour == clBufferStopBackground)
3723  {
3724  Number = 0xb3;
3725  }
3726  else if(Colour == clCallOnBackground)
3727  {
3728  Number = 0xbf;
3729  }
3730  else if(Colour == clCrashedBackground) // covers DerailedBackground because that has the same colour number
3731  {
3732  Number = 0xb4;
3733  }
3734  else if(Colour == clNormalBackground)
3735  {
3736  Number = 0xac;
3737  }
3738  else if(Colour == clSignallerStopped)
3739  {
3740  Number = 0xcf;
3741  }
3742  else if(Colour == clSignalStopBackground)
3743  {
3744  Number = 0x66;
3745  }
3746  else if(Colour == clSPADBackground)
3747  {
3748  Number = 0xd2;
3749  }
3750  else if(Colour == clStationStopBackground)
3751  {
3752  Number = 0xb2;
3753  }
3754  else if(Colour == clStoppedTrainInFront)
3755  {
3756  Number = 0x83;
3757  }
3758  else if(Colour == clTRSBackground)
3759  {
3760  Number = 0xd1;
3761  }
3762  else if(Colour == clTrainFailedBackground) // added at v2.4.0
3763  {
3764  Number = 0xc0;
3765  }
3766  else
3767  {
3768  Number = 0xac; // normal background
3769  }
3770 
3771 
3772 /*
3773  switch(Colour)
3774  {
3775  case clB0G0R0: // black
3776  Number = 0x0;
3777  break;
3778 
3779  case clB5G5R5: // white
3780  Number = 0xd7;
3781  break;
3782 
3783  case clBufferAttentionNeeded:
3784  Number = 0x23;
3785  break;
3786 
3787  case clBufferStopBackground:
3788  Number = 0xb3;
3789  break;
3790 
3791  case clCallOnBackground:
3792  Number = 0xbf;
3793  break;
3794 
3795  case clCrashedBackground: // covers DerailedBackground because that has the same colour number
3796  Number = 0xb4;
3797  break;
3798 
3799  case clNormalBackground:
3800  Number = 0xac;
3801  break;
3802 
3803  case clSignallerStopped:
3804  Number = 0xcf;
3805  break;
3806 
3807  case clSignalStopBackground:
3808  Number = 0x66;
3809  break;
3810 
3811  case clSPADBackground:
3812  Number = 0xd2;
3813  break;
3814 
3815  case clStationStopBackground:
3816  Number = 0xb2;
3817  break;
3818 
3819  case clStoppedTrainInFront:
3820  Number = 0x83;
3821  break;
3822 
3823  case clTRSBackground:
3824  Number = 0xd1;
3825  break;
3826 
3827  case clTrainFailedBackground: // added at v2.4.0
3828  Number = 0xc0;
3829  break;
3830 
3831  default:
3832  // UnicodeString MessageStr = "Can't find required colour - normal background colour will be used.");
3833  // Application->MessageBox(MessageStr.c_str(), L"", MB_OK); don't give message as can be called when operating (need StopTTClockMessage)
3834  Number = 0xac; // normal background
3835  break;
3836 */
3837  Utilities->CallLogPop(2104);
3838  return(Number);
3839 }

4435 void TRailGraphics::SetUpAllDerivitiveGraphics(TColor TransparentColour)
4436 {
4437  for(int x = 0; x < 30; x++)
4438  {
4439  LinkPrefDirGraphicsPtr[x]->TransparentColor = TransparentColour;
4440  LinkNonSigRouteGraphicsPtr[x]->TransparentColor = TransparentColour;
4441  LinkSigRouteGraphicsPtr[x]->TransparentColor = TransparentColour;
4442  LinkRouteAutoSigsGraphicsPtr[x]->TransparentColor = TransparentColour;
4443  }
4444  for(int x = 0; x < 12; x++)
4445  {
4446  BridgePrefDirGraphicsPtr[x]->TransparentColor = TransparentColour;
4447  BridgeNonSigRouteGraphicsPtr[x]->TransparentColor = TransparentColour;
4448  BridgeSigRouteGraphicsPtr[x]->TransparentColor = TransparentColour;
4449  BridgeRouteAutoSigsGraphicsPtr[x]->TransparentColor = TransparentColour;
4450  }
4451 
4452 /*
4453  EXArray with associated Tag numbers:-
4454  {4,6} 1,{2,8} 2, //horizontal & vertical
4455  {2,4} 6,{6,2} 5,{8,6} 3,{4,8}, 4 //sharp curves
4456  {1,6} 22,{3,8} 24,{9,4} 21,{7,2} 27,{1,8} 25,{3,4} 23,{9,2} 26,{7,6}, 20 //loose curves
4457  {1,9} 19,{3,7} 18, //forward & reverse diagonals
4458 
4459  int Bridge EXArray with Tag numbers:-
4460  {4,6} 48,{2,8} 49,{1,9} 50,{3,7} 51,
4461  {1,9} 52,{3,7} 56,{1,9} 57,{3,7} 53,
4462  {2,8} 54,{4,6} 59,{2,8} 55,{4,6} 58
4463 
4464  reverse direction same in each case
4465 */
4466
